-- American Express profit doubles as US holiday shoppers spend more
-- By Aman Shah in Bangalore
-- Thu Jan 16, 2014 04:11PM EST
-- None



Jan 16 (Reuters) - Credit card company American Express Co's <AXP.N> quarterly profit more than doubled as it gained from higher consumer spending during the U.S. holiday season.

The company's net income rose to $1.31 billion, or $1.21 per share, for the fourth quarter ended Dec. 31, from $637 million, or 56 cents per share, a year earlier. [ID:nBw7fgSnpa]